    "A New and Concise Bible Dictionary": "Zech. 13: 8,",
    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And he washed his face, etc.] From the tears on it, that it might not be discerned that he had been weeping: and went out; of his chamber into the room again, where his brethren were: and refrained himself; from weeping, or showing any excess of passion, love, joy, etc. and said, set on bread; gave orders to his servants to bring in dinner, and set it upon the table; bread, as before, being put for all kind of food.\nVer."
